import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Miles_per_Gallon'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['Weight_in_lbs', 'Miles_per_Gallon']]
    plt.scatter(data['Weight_in_lbs'], data['Miles_per_Gallon'])
    plt.xlabel('Weight_in_lbs')
    plt.ylabel('Miles_per_Gallon')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Weight_in_lbs and Miles_per_Gallon?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Horsepower'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Horsepower'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Horsepower'])
    plt.hist(data['Horsepower'], bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['Horsepower'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['Horsepower'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Horsepower?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Cylinders'] = data['Cylinders'].astype(str)
    data = data.groupby('Cylinders').size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar(data['Cylinders'], data['counts'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Cylinders')
    ax.set_ylabel('Count')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Cylinders?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Origin'].value_counts().plot(kind='pie', autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Origin?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
